	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston&#44; S. C.</placeName> <date>Feb. 25. 1855</date>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Rev. Is. Leeser</addressee>&#44; <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Dear Sir&#47;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;My sister&#45;<lb/>in&#45;law&#44; <persName>Mrs. Jacob. I. Moses</persName> having left for <placeName>N York</placeName>&#44; you<lb/> will be kind enough to send the Occident again to her<lb/> direction&#44; <placeName>419 Fourth Str. New York</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Hoping that you will not be offended&#44; I take<lb/> the liberty of calling your attention to a typographical error<lb/> in your version of the Bible&#44; which I happened to find this<lb/> morning.  It is in Deut. VIII&#44; V. 17&#44; where I read&#58;<lb/> &#8220;the strength of <hi rend="underline">thy</hi> hand&#44;&#8221; instead of &#8220;the strength<lb/> of <hi rend="underline">my</hi> hand&#44;&#8221; <add>Hebrew</add>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">What do you think of <persName>Dr Wise&#39;s</persName> project with re&#45;<lb/>gard to a &#8220;Conference.&#8221;  Judging from the contents of<lb/> a letter which you wrote to me about 18 months ago&#44;<lb/> you must <del>have</del> be in favor of it.  Or have you changed<lb/> your opinion&#63;  Is it not worth <hi rend="underline">trying</hi> at least&#63;</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">Most respectfully&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Dr M Mayer</persName></p>
		</body>
